snippet.textDisplay:
Tennis Australia gave the exemption to Djokovic to play in the tennis tournament - which is fine - but in doing so Tennis Australia is assuming that he would be let into the country by the federal government.  These are two different things.  

When arriving at the airport in Melbourne, Djokovic could not prove that he had a legitimate exemption - to enter the country!
And so the government cancelled his visa - to enter the country.     

Djokovic then decided to challenge the Australian government and its laws  - and he did this two times. 
So it became a long-drawn out legal process - because Djokovic chose to challenge the Australian laws.  

The most important and relevant question that remains unanswered is:   
Who are the parties that conspired to get the No 1 player in the world into Australia, regardless of, and in contravention of, Australia's migration laws?  And is Tennis Australia or Djokovic in any way involved in this conspiracy?
